history.content:
A lot of my friends really praise EE 120 as it has applications everywhere. It's really math-heavy though.

EE(CS) 126 and 127 are pretty core too.

--------------

Another vote for 120 here! Taking it now and really enjoying it (Babak is a wonderful lecturer). It's most useful if you're interested in controls, signal processing, or other math-heavy disciplines of EE. I hear good things about 128 as well, and 105 is pretty core if you're interested in circuits.

--------------

I'll also advocate for 120. Super cool class that gives you a taste of the various areas of EE, and extends a lot of 16B stuff to a deeper level. After taking it you'll know what (if any) more advanced EE upper divs (123, 128, etc.) you want to take.
